04:19.306 --> 04:27.535
You've gone through something, you're going through something, maybe it's a valley, a pit, something that you're in right now and you don't feel like it's ever gonna end or you're gonna be delivered from it.

04:28.276 --> 04:29.617
And David says, how long?

04:30.158 --> 04:32.681
Verse four, turn, oh Lord, deliver my life.

04:33.221 --> 04:35.604
Save me for the sake of your steadfast love.

04:36.545 --> 04:38.487
For in death there is no remembrance of you.

04:38.908 --> 04:40.529
In Shio, who will give you praise?

04:41.130 --> 04:44.594
And then he says in verse six, I am weary with my moaning.

04:45.314 --> 04:46.896
I am weary with my moaning.

04:47.397 --> 04:49.720
Every night I flood my bed with tears.

04:50.201 --> 04:52.424
I drenched my couch with my weeping.

04:53.245 --> 04:55.008
This is a man that's going through a whole lot.

04:56.069 --> 05:02.879
And I dare to venture to say that there are some men and women in this room and watching online who are going through a whole lot.

05:03.179 --> 05:05.082
And you can say my heart is troubled.

05:05.603 --> 05:07.405
Even my soul is troubled.

05:08.827 --> 05:13.554
And it's to you that I want to preach, not that the others who are not going through anything, right now,

05:13.954 --> 05:21.826
I would bypass, but I want to speak into your life the Word of God so that you can have encouragement and hope this morning.

05:21.846 --> 05:22.267
Are you ready?

05:23.749 --> 05:25.832
Okay, sit up straight, right?

05:26.232 --> 05:27.214
