05:38.431 --> 05:43.218
Surely goodness and mercy shall follow me all the days of my life.

05:43.618 --> 05:46.801
And I shall dwell in the house of the Lord temporarily.

05:51.006 --> 05:53.909
I've titled the seventh message, how to come out of your valley.

05:55.511 --> 05:56.872
How to come out of your valley.

05:59.475 --> 06:00.877
Okay, I'm going to get real a bit bold here.

06:02.599 --> 06:10.127
How many people would say that you have been in a valley recently or are in a valley of some sort?

06:11.188 --> 06:11.749
Raise your hand.

06:12.489 --> 06:13.010
Raise your hand.

06:13.986 --> 06:18.531
many, many, many, many hands.

06:18.551 --> 06:23.618
David says, surely goodness and mercy shall follow me all the days of my life, and I shall dwell in the house of the Lord.

06:23.858 --> 06:25.300
How do you come out of your valley?

06:26.401 --> 06:27.122
How do you do that?

06:27.743 --> 06:30.566
Well, David mentions valleys all throughout scripture.

06:30.586 --> 06:43.922
He mentions the shadow of death, which would probably be the darkest of all valleys, the shadow of death, verse 4 of Psalm 23, valleys in the Bible, not only are topographical and geographical, but they're also spiritual.

06:44.802 --> 06:46.624
