07:05.250 --> 07:06.291
Over nine foot tall.

07:06.311 --> 07:08.474
Guess who what his name was, right?

07:08.494 --> 07:09.395
The valley of Elah.

07:09.816 --> 07:11.378
How about the valley of Eschkal?

07:12.194 --> 07:12.975
What happened there?

07:13.015 --> 07:16.599
Well, that was where the spies were looking into the promised land.

07:17.320 --> 07:19.982
And there were two that came back and said, we can take the promised land.

07:20.003 --> 07:21.004
Do you remember who those two were?

07:21.885 --> 07:27.671
Joshua and Caleb and the other were saying that we're like grasshoppers and there are giants in the land.

07:28.572 --> 07:30.394
How about the Valley of Jezreel?

07:30.434 --> 07:32.376
That's where King Saul was defeated.

07:33.497 --> 07:37.502
Valley is not only a topographical and geographical, they're spiritual in nature.

07:38.763 --> 07:41.586
There are things that God wants to accomplish in and through

07:41.698 --> 07:44.922
But let me just say it like this to begin with as a way of introduction.

07:46.303 --> 07:48.666
All valleys lead to some form of victory.

07:50.287 --> 08:00.879
All valleys, and so those hands that went up, there's victory that's coming to you not only in your valley, but as you exit your valley and to what God has after that experience for you.

08:01.660 --> 08:02.721
So hold on to hope.

08:04.243 --> 08:05.164
Don't dread.

08:05.224 --> 08:07.526
Don't fear.

08:09.088 --> 08:10.930
Certainly don't wander away.

08:11.458 --> 08:12.219
and don't give up.

08:13.681 --> 08:14.923
This is going to be a word for you.

08:14.943 --> 08:16.525
I pray it's an encouraging word.

08:16.825 --> 08:19.349
This place of pain is preparation for what's next.

08:19.369 --> 08:22.273
You'll see on the screen a man who's one of my heroes.

08:22.293 --> 08:23.414
He went to heaven.

08:23.815 --> 08:25.758
He went to be with the Lord many, many years ago.

08:25.798 --> 08:26.739
