And so nobody getting old road rage at

11:20.802 --> 11:24.047
you know, cross-way mill for trying to find your way out of this parking lot.

11:24.428 --> 11:25.850
But there are some verses of Scripture.

11:25.870 --> 11:26.691
I need you to see.

11:26.711 --> 11:28.814
So get your Bibles ready.

11:28.834 --> 11:30.317
We're going to turn pretty quickly.

11:30.677 --> 11:31.799
Here's principle number one.

11:31.819 --> 11:34.924
This is what I see that David learned on how to get out of your valley.

11:34.964 --> 11:36.807
Remember the providences of the Lord.

11:37.488 --> 11:41.674
Number one, remember the providences of the Lord.

11:41.714 --> 11:46.802
He says this, surely goodness and mercy shall follow me all the days of my life.

11:47.266 --> 11:49.309
How was it that David was able to say this?

11:49.610 --> 11:50.731
Why did he say that?

11:51.212 --> 11:52.774
Let's ask the texts and questions.

11:53.555 --> 11:58.643
Remember, valleys aren't permanent places of residence, but temporary places meant to test us.

